{
  "texts": [
    "DAgger is used as it mitigates compounding errors caused by distributional shift and has been widely applied in robot locomotion and navigation [36].",
    "All the randomly generated embodiments interact with the environment in simulation using Nav-ACT.",
    "Namely, at each timestep t, Nav-ACT generates an action sequence 𝐀. and the first action from the sequence, 𝑎.",
    "[0], is executed.",
    "At the same time, for each robot embodiment, the corresponding expert policy π K is queried to generate an expert action 𝑎 L,.. To enable action chunking, the expert actions are stacked into action chunks 𝐀 $,."
  ]
}